This set covers all edges (adjacent pairs) in the grid. 4. **Verification**: - Each possible rectangle (edge) is covered by at least one of the guessed squares in the set {1, 3, 7, 9}. - For example, the rectangle covering squares 1 and 2 is covered by square 1; the rectangle covering squares 3 and 5 is covered by square 3, and so on. 5. **Conclusion**: - After verifying that smaller sets (e.g., size 3) fail to cover all edges, we conclude that the minimal vertex cover is indeed 4. Thus, the minimum number of turns needed to ensure at least one guessed square is covered by the hidden rectangle is \(\boxed{4}\).
